about.summary: Functions that implement the known population median test.

name: r-kpmt
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-kpmt
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/kpmt_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/kpmt/kpmt_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 6342ad02c93bfa7a764d028821bb6115bb8bc8c55b057a5860736cc0e034a295

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1003
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrixstats
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-matrixstats

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('kpmt')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('kpmt')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=kpmt
  license: MIT
  summary: Functions that implement the known population median test.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: 
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE
    
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
